# Auto-commit and auto-push policy

**Precedence:** In this repository, this rule overrides `OPERATING_RULES.md` ôÏ Git and any generic Cursor user instruction to "ask before commit" or "push only when asked" when the current task or plan is **authorized and complete**. Paste [`.cursor/USER_RULES_GIT_SNIPPET.md`](../../.cursor/USER_RULES_GIT_SNIPPET.md) into global user rules if agents still hesitate.

## When to auto-commit

**Standing authorization:** commit and push to feature branches when the task is done and the gate passesãdo not ask ãmay I commit?ã each time (see `COMMIT_POLICY_V1.md`).

- All todos / requested work for the current task or plan are complete.
- **Pushable commit gate** has passed (see Test alignment below).
- Before committing, the agent must always:
  - Show `git status`, `git diff`, `git log -1 --oneline`.
  - Propose **one commit by default** for the task; split into multiple commits only when changes are clearly separate (e.g. docs vs code vs tests).

## What not to commit (safety exclusions)

- Never auto-commit secrets:
  - `.env`, `*.env*`, credentials, keys, tokens, or similar sensitive material.
- Never auto-commit obvious generated noise unless explicitly requested:
  - `artifacts/`, `.pytest_cache/`, `__pycache__/`, `*.sqlite*`, `*.db`, log files, or other large/generated outputs.
- Do not change git config.
- Do not use `git commit --amend` unless the user explicitly requests it.

## Auto-push behavior (branch-aware)

### Non-main branches

- After auto-commit on any branch **other than** `main` / `master`, the agent should **auto-push** to the branchãs existing upstream.
- If the current branch has no upstream yet, the first push should be `git push -u origin HEAD` (or equivalent for the default remote).
- **After push**, if there is no open PR to `main` for this branch, **open one** (`gh pr create --base main --head <branch>`). GitHub will add the `automerge` label ([`label-pr-automerge.yml`](../../.github/workflows/label-pr-automerge.yml)); when the **CI** workflow ([`ci.yml`](../../.github/workflows/ci.yml)) completes **`success`**ãi.e. both **`CI / pytest`** and **`CI / docker_entrypoint`** passã[`merge-on-green.yml`](../../.github/workflows/merge-on-green.yml) squash-merges to `main` and **Deploy VPS** can run. Do not stop at ãpushed feature branchã when the intent is to ship.
- Preconditions for auto-push on non-main branches:
  - Pushable commit gate passed (ruff + full pytest, or docs-only exception).
  - The working tree is clean except for the intended changes.
  - No force push; fast-forward only.

### After merge or rebase of `origin/main`

When `git merge origin/main` or `git rebase origin/main` completes on a **non-main** branch (clean tree, no conflict markers):

1. Run **`python scripts/run_pushable_gate.py`** ã it auto-includes commits **ahead of upstream** (not only diff vs `main`). Use **`--pre-push`** when you only want the unpushed commit range.
2. **`git push`** (or `git push -u origin HEAD` if no upstream). Do **not** stop at "merge succeeded" or ask "want me to push?"
3. If no open PR to `main` for this branch, **open one** per non-main rules above.

This applies even when the user only asked to "sync main" ã syncing is complete only after gate + push (unless push is blocked: force-push, remote rejection, or gate failure).

### `main` / `master` branches

- Same gate as any pushable commit: `python -m ruff check src tests scripts` and `python -m pytest -q`.
- If the repository uses **PR-only** delivery to `main` (see [docs/SOP/GITHUB_ZERO_TOUCH_MERGE.md](../../docs/SOP/GITHUB_ZERO_TOUCH_MERGE.md)), **do not** auto-push directly to `main`. Push a **feature branch** and open a PR so GitHub runs the full **CI** workflow (pytest + docker_entrypoint) before merge.
- No secrets / artifacts in the commit; no force push or history rewrite.

## When not to auto-push

The agent must NOT auto-push when:

- Push would require `--force`, history rewrite, or unsafe conflict resolution.
- Remote rejects the push (branch protection, required checks) ã surface the error; do not retry with riskier options.
- Ruff or full pytest failed, or the gate was not run for non-docs-only code changes.

## Test alignment (canonical)

Authoritative detail: [docs/SOP/COMMIT_POLICY_V1.md](../../docs/SOP/COMMIT_POLICY_V1.md) and [docs/SOP/TESTING_TIERS_V1.md](../../docs/SOP/TESTING_TIERS_V1.md).

### WIP commit (fast gate)

```bash
python scripts/run_pushable_gate.py
```

Runs ruff + fast pytest (`-m "not witness and not slow"`).

### Before push (full gate ã required)

```bash
python scripts/run_pushable_gate.py --pre-push
```

Matches **`CI / pytest`** (ruff + full `pytest -q`). Run before every push; do not substitute targeted pytest only.

### Docs-only exception

If the change set is **only** under `docs/`, pytest is not required; ruff is optional unless `scripts/` or `src/` changed.

### Implied-lab UI (PR / merge, not commit)

If the task touched `src/viz/**` or UI smoke scripts, run smoke before PR merge (see `TESTING_TIERS_V1.md`):

```bash
python scripts/run_implied_lab_ui_smoke.py
```

Use dual smoke only when harness-wide or dual chrome changed. Do not block commit on smoke (environment-sensitive).

### Merge to `main`

GitHub **CI** = **`CI / pytest`** (ruff + full pytest) **and** **`CI / docker_entrypoint`** (Docker + Streamlit smoke). Local `--pre-push` gate should match pytest + ruff before push; docker smoke runs on GitHub unless you replicate it locally.
